Unfocused HP is a bit high I think, more like 8k, but otherwise, yes.
<br />

<br />
This is provided they keep the same (lousy) scaling of focus effects on the pets.  i.e. The best focus would only add 15 damage or so.
<br />

<br />
Of course, I would rather have the pet be the majority of the DPS than the Magician itself.  60/40 split, like it used to be.  I don't know if you were around for it, but we used to have to fight our pets for XP, try and out-damage them.  On raids if it was called to kill pets, I threw a huge hissy fit.
<br />

<br />
Today, if a raid calls to kill pets (rarely happens, but I'm illustrating a point here) I just think "meh" and do it.  Because it's only about 20% of my damage output these days.  I don't feel entirely worthless without a pet, now I just feel mildly weaker.
