				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The reason I want the water pet to do more DPS from the front and back of the mob is because the water pet is a pure DPS pet, it doesn't do anything else, it really cant tank, and does not have the utility of the other pets (earth has root, air has stun).
<br />

<br />
The reason I am suggesting for the earth pet to do the same damage as the air pet is because earth comes from a Glowing Muramite Rune, and air comes from a minor muramite rune. Glowing runes are much harder to obtain, so  just thought it would balance the effort vs reward ratio to make them do about the same DPS, while earth has a clear tanking advantage.
<br />

<br />
I notice you say I want them to hit for 150-170 ect, this is not necessarily what I want, what I want is that when we parse our pet's, to see the numbers come out to about 150-170 DPS, this can be done by either raising max hit, or raising the accuracy of our pets IMO.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490410&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dalren Fieryblade, Invictus Verite</a>
