			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One way I think pet dps could be safely raised, and would make us (or our summons at least) a little more wanted is to increase the proc rate and proc damage on the summoned weapons.
<br />

<br />
The cleric hammers have an insane proc rate.  Greatstaff of the Four Winds has an increased proc rate, as does the Obsidian Schimitar of war.  Why can't our pet weapons have an increased proc rate as well?  Make them proc at about the rate of the old mage epic and up the damage a fair amount...like maybe up to 175-200.  Hell...make us use different pet weapons for different resists if you have to.
<br />

<br />
I would like to see the Air pet producing about 150 dps just from melee alone.  The water pet should be about 170 dps melee only from the front and 200-210 from the rear with pure melee.  
<br />

<br />
As far as hp or defensive capabilities of the pets.....its hard for me to say.  I think some more pet specific AA as far as damage mitigation and whatnot would help in this area.  Maybe more AA for more pet hp?  We had one set of AA like this....but stopping it at 500hp isnt all that much.  More pet specific AA please (if SoE isn't going to buff the power of the pets directly like they said they would)
<br />

<br />
Maybe, on the pet belt, add an accuracy focus?  Would that help mage pets land more hits?  Hell....that might solve the pet dps problems right there if they connected more hits with the mobs.  Something useful like 100% or 150% accuracy.  Or whatever % puts pets around the dps numbers I suggested.
<br />

<br />
Regardless of whether pets are buffed and balanced directly, or you make us do it by gaining more AA....just do it.  If you want me to work for it...fine.  But put it in the game, and soon.  Not in the next expansion only.  I agree in part with most of the posters on this site....to release an expansion that makes the new pets FINALLY balance with content one or two expansions ago is sad.  Implement the AA and the items or spells to correct this.
<br />

<br />
Also....a pet Cheal please...and shorter recast times on our current heals.<br />_________________<br />Llassar Wurmburner
<br />
65 Mage of the Nameless</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
