				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as my views on the pet thing (since I know you all have been holding your breath)...
<br />

<br />
Air: I want air to do ~110 UN-focused and have a better ATK rating...so he misses less often.  I think that would fix a lot of the DPS issues rather than jacking up the damage per hit.  Focus effects should also play a bigger role in enchancing the pet....DPoC certainly less, comparatively less, since its so easy to get.
<br />

<br />
Water:  I want the 66 pet to have the ability to automatically go to the back of the mob after 2 or 3 melee rounds of not being in the back.....and not change any hit totals for it.  With it auto-adjusting to the back, the DPS will automatically increase.
<br />

<br />
Fire: He sux.  Change him to a ~90 unfocused pet and make him only cast certain offensive spells during combat.  So he does toe to toe, but also will stop for 8 seconds and cast an Ice Comet.
<br />

<br />
Earth:  I think he should hit for ~125 unfocused and have close to 10k hps...with better mitigation.  I think that the Earth pet should, pretty much, be THE choice when soloing...especially since he is level 70.  Fact is, that pet is the WARRIOR pet, so he should function like one.
<br />

<br />
As for HPs:
<br />

<br />
Air - maybe 500 more unfocused with a bigger ramping scale
<br />
Water - Same as today...less of a tank
<br />
Fire - even less than water...he is a caster.
<br />
Earth - I would say a good 1.5 to 2k more...he is a warrior after all.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
