<br />

<br />
That would require rewriting a lot of the code as it is just an NPC.  And even if it did only cast spells I would only use it on very rare occasions.  You all know the thing would still be stupid enough to stand inside Fennin's AE range while it casted its spell for instance.  And if not that then we would all complain about how it casts a fire nuke on fennin half the time.  
<br />

<br />
I like having a pet that will tank after the tank or entire group wipes (i've soloed 2 WoS mobs that were slowed before group wiped before.)  I'd rather see the fire pet turned into the melee machine it was at earlier levels.  Take away its spells, give it dps higher than water pet, less hps than water pet, and more avoidance.
<br />

<br />
As for the other pets:  Only new pet I have now is 66 Air.  I'm loving him except that he can generate aggro so much that when he pushes mob back 2 inches away from the MT he will have aggro instead of the mob running back to the MT.  This even happens with our best aggro warriors chain taunting, bellowing and whatnot.  I would like to see the dps turned up on him a little more though.  Hits for 125 would be good and min hit should go up about 15 points as well.  Hit points and avoidance seem to be where they should be.  Hard to keep him up with PoP heal, but yeah, thats how it should be with an old heal spell.  
<br />

<br />
Only further balancing I would like to see would be summoned items to be more streamline (one spell for girdle, two flaming swords and all the focus gear we can make.  This could be a level 70 spell.  Girdle btw would have 15% haste on it and 750 hps while sword's proc would be less resistable and 200 prismatic damage.)  I love giving my pet all the focus items especially since now they have some AC and 45 hps each but in reality i'd never do this unless they were included in the "pet pack" spell.  And they better not summon inside of a bag, i'd rather have all the items lined up on my cursor so i can clickX4, [give], clickX4 etc..<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=805629" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arch Mage Magusmaximus Burninator</a>
