				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Saying my Airpet hits for 110 + 62dmg shield + Air-ele strike is wrong.
<br />

<br />
The pet is not hitting for 62 ever. It is only when the pet is hit ITSELF that that is factored in, and then only because the magician casts the dmg shield on the pet. It is NOT innate. Nor are the pet proc weapons innate.
<br />

<br />
We are looking at pet DPS. Not pet dps when it's tanking an unslowed mob that quads for 80dmg 3times a second with pet affinity and a bard singing their max dmg shield song. Pet DPS. Send pet on the mob with only our own burnout buff and parse it.
<br />

<br />
I want to see the pet parse via only melee in the 140-150dps range. Add in 6dps for the summoned pet weapons on exp mobs. Add 6dps (75dmg/12second recast) from the ele strike. For a total of ~160dps for the airpet.
<br />

<br />
Add in an extra 40dps for waterpet from behind, and 20dps from the front (chaotic backstab anyone? let it backstab from anywhere, but hits from min unless it has the mobs back, just like a true rogue).
<br />

<br />
Earthpet, just because it is 4 levels higher of a spell than the airpet, and significantly harder to acquire, should do the same dps as the airpet.
<br />

<br />
Firepet as it currently exists isn't worth wasting an ethereal parchment on, much less a Muramite Rune. Completely recode the thing to make it useful or delete it entirely. Giving us a broken useless pet for the past 4years (has been broken since Kunark in 2000) does nothing but further upset the community.<br />_________________<br />Master Elementalist Sebboh Nivlac
<br />
Officer of Only the Brave, Veeshan
